\begin{document}
}{}\begin{equation*}\left\{ {\begin{array}{*{20}{c}} {E({X^2}) = cf}\\ {{\sigma ^2}({X^2}) = 2{c^2}f} \end{array}} \right.\end{equation*}\end{document}

The c and f can be obtained accordingly:
\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym} 
