}{}\begin{equation*}f = \frac{{2{{[E({X^2})]}^2}}}{{{\sigma ^2}({X^2})}} = \frac{{2{k^2}}}{{2k + 2\sum\limits_{i < j} {\sum {{\mathop{\rm cov}} (x_i^2,x_j^2)} } }}\end{equation*}\end{document}
Let h = 1/c, we define the W-test, with a scalar h before the X2, as:
(2)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
